    "LogR uses a sigmoid function to represent the data, just like lR assumes that the data follow a linear model as in Eq. 2 and shown in Fig.",
    "16 [182].gðxÞ ¼ 1 1 þ e À xð2ÞLogistic regression can be categorized based on the following categories:1.",
    "Binomial: There are just two potential kinds for the target variable: ''0'' or ''1,'' which can indicate ''win'' versus ''loss,'' ''pass'' vs. ''fail,'' ''dead'' vs. ''alive,'' and so on. 2.",
    "Multinomial: The target variable can have three or more non-ordered types (i.e., the types have no quantitative importance), such as ''illness A'' vs. ''disease B'' vs. ''disease C.'' 3.Ordinal: it deals with ordered categories of target variables.",
    "A test score, for example, can be classified as ''extremely poor,'' ''bad,'' ''good,'' or ''very good.''"
